240
00:32:07,853 --> 00:32:15,297
but auto technology, culinary arts, those are tougher to create temporary modular classrooms to accommodate.

241
00:32:15,437 --> 00:32:28,923
So for those students, when their section of the building is being renovated in this scenario, there's the potential that they would have to be offsite, potentially in a community partner location where they could have space that's adequate for instruction.

242
00:32:29,323 --> 00:32:34,225
So there's transportation, there's loss on learning time, there's impact to educational experience as well.

243
00:32:34,985 --> 00:32:37,247
that needs to be considered for those CTE students.

244
00:32:38,348 --> 00:32:58,363
And I did not mention specifically the modular classrooms for the A, 8.1 option as well, but it is very similar, actually the same in terms of the number of classrooms required, because we would be moving around the building, renovating it in a similar way in addition, in this case, to adding stories on top.

