00:56:08,120 --> 00:56:21,472
exploring everything from selling the building and using the proceeds to acknowledging that Medford does not have lots of land and space for the kinds of programming that is desired in the community.

427
00:56:22,813 --> 00:56:25,896
And could that building be a home to something else?

428
00:56:26,597 --> 00:56:27,858
All is very much on the table.

429
00:56:27,958 --> 00:56:31,401
So we can't just simply say we're not going to do these things.

430
00:56:31,761 --> 00:56:32,382
Those would be

431
00:56:33,022 --> 00:56:44,771
Those would be programming cuts or relocation decisions, so that they're substantially more complicated than just sort of this group saying, we don't want to build a space for it.

432
00:56:45,312 --> 00:56:56,961
There's much more conversation about if that is the case, like, where do those programs go and how do we carry on things like kindergarten registration and

